              "url": "https://photos.reinhardluvr69.com/photos/9a80c1ea-9583-4f7e-ba08-e1e8f364f26e.jpg",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "https://photos.reinhardluvr69.com/photos/9a80c1ea-9583-4f7e-ba08-e1e8f364f26e.jpg"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "But…"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "I'm insane enough to descend."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "It wasn't part of the plan, but I saw a group of Filipinos going down the stairs so I also thought of doing it, too."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": null,
              "url": "https://photos.reinhardluvr69.com/photos/fa0b00a2-79cf-46ac-96b9-d1df81d4afa3.jpg",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "https://photos.reinhardluvr69.com/photos/fa0b00a2-79cf-46ac-96b9-d1df81d4afa3.jpg"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Whenever I'm descending through wooden stairs, I always forget I have bit of a fear feeling its slight wobble. So, I held tight to the rail and kept a constant eye contact downwards keeping a close eye on the wooden steps that slightly blur both from the dark and my own fear. It was awkward going down with poles in between the guardrails, so I had to stop when my hands reach those poles, hold the new start of the rail with my non-dominant hand, move my dominant hand on the new rail, then proceed moving downwards."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "I should've known not to go down after seeing how frozen the part below was. I didn't take a picture of it because my phone was dead, but the path to the next dry stairs were completely frozen. Rather than detouring two or three kilometers elsewhere, I sat down on ice and slid myself downwards. One of the girls, that didn't speak English, gave me a go encouraging me to slide down, so I did it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": null,
              "url": "https://photos.reinhardluvr69.com/photos/9fa062b2-db26-47c0-9644-9ad2737e320c.jpg?with-description=true",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "https://photos.reinhardluvr69.com/photos/9fa062b2-db26-47c0-9644-9ad2737e320c.jpg?with-description=true"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "After a few more zigzaging slope downwards and encountering closed stairs, I finally reached non-slippery civilization."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
